\section{Discussion}
\label{sec:discussion}

\subsection{Practical Implications for Market Design}

\textbf{Reserve Pricing.} In SCED-based markets, the reserve shadow price $\mu_z^*$ equals the marginal cost of procuring an additional MW of reserves in zone $z$. Learned sets produce more accurate $\mu_z^*$ by encoding the true correlation structure, leading to more efficient price signals.

\textbf{Renewable Integration.} As renewable penetration increases, forecast error correlations change---solar errors are highly correlated during cloud events, wind errors depend on weather fronts. Context-dependent uncertainty sets $\bL_\phi(\bxi)$ adapt to these patterns in real time.

\subsection{Computational Considerations}

